title: Neds Corner - Insects, spiders and other invertebrates
description: Area incorporating the Neds Corner property (Trust for Nature) and the adjoining Murray River frontage.

items.title: Aglaosoma variegata
items.content_text:
Large, hairy caterpillar found feeding on Cattle Bush (Alectryon oleifolius subsp. canescens). Size similar to adult pointer finger, both in length and girth.
Thanks to Cathy Powers and Peter Marriott for identification.
